comments: Siakam (TOR) moves forward to avoid the screen and initiates marginal contact with Grant (DET) on the perimeter.
Boucher (TOR) maintains a legal guarding position on Bey (DET) during the drive and the contact is incidental.
Bey (DET) hops consecutively on the same foot upon gathering the ball.
Achiuwa (TOR) is drawn into the air towards Cunningham (DET) and marginal contact occurs at the start of his drive.
Boucher (TOR) jumps towards Cunningham (DET) to contest the shot attempt and incidental contact occurs after the release that does not affect his shot attempt.
Cunningham (DET) crosses midcourt within eight seconds.
Siakam (TOR) briefly engages and disengages with Grant (DET) on the perimeter and the contact is marginal.
Boucher (TOR) and Barnes (TOR) both make incidental contact with Bey (DET) following the release of his jump shot attempt.

Siakam (TOR) extends his off-arm into Cunningham (DET), but Cunningham's momentum is already carrying him in the same direction and he is not dislodged from his position as a result of the marginal contact.
Trent Jr. (TOR) maintains a legal guarding position while defending Joseph (DET) on the perimeter.
Trent Jr. (TOR) legally contests Cunningham's (DET) jump shot attempt.  Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Stewart (DET) engages with Achiuwa (TOR), who grabs and holds him, affecting his ability to get to the rebound.  A loose ball foul should be assessed to Achiuwa instead of Stewart.
Stewart (DET) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Barnes (TOR) and absorbs the contact.
Barnes (TOR) makes marginal contact with Bey (DET) that does not affect his driving shot attempt.
Trent Jr. (TOR) drives through Grant (DET) and dislodges him from his legal guarding position.
Achiuwa (TOR) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Joseph (DET) and absorbs the contact.  Joseph briefly grabs Achiuwa following the screen but immediately releases.
Cunningham (DET) cleanly blocks Trent Jr.'s (TOR) shot attempt at the basket and any contact is incidental.
Joseph (DET) initiates contact with Achiuwa (TOR) that affects his ability to get to the rebound.
